data-triple-N3.o: "Podkarpackie Voivodeship or Podkarpacie Province, also known as Subcarpathian Voivodeship, is a voivodeship, or province, in extreme-southeastern Poland. Its administrative capital and largest city is Rzeszow. (Historically Lwow was the administrative center of this part of Poland, but after 1945, when Lwow became part of the Soviet Union, that city's role was relinquished to Rzeszow."@en
